A x B = {(1, 2), (1, 3), (2, 2), (2, 3)}
B x A = {(2, 1), (2, 2), (3, 1), (3, 2)}

Now, we find the intersection of A x B and B x A:

A x B ∩ B x A = {(2, 2)}

So, the intersection of A x B and B x A is the set {(2, 2)}.
